E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20order%20says%20no%20tractor%20trolleys%20or%20trucks%20transporting%20people%20or%20materials%2C%20especially%20those%20carrying%20sticks%20or%20any%20items%20that%20can%20be%20used%20as%20a%20weapon%20of%20violence%2C%20shall%20be%20allowed%20to%20enter%20Delhi.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20order%20also%20bars%20collecting%20or%20carrying%20any%20form%20or%20explosives%2C%20boulders%2C%20acid%2C%20petrol%2C%20sodawater%20bottles%20or%20any%20item%20that%20can%20be%20used%20to%20cause%20danger%20to%20anyone.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWedding%20and%20funeral%20processions%20and%20religious%20rallies%20are%20allowed%20as%20long%20as%20they%20are%20organised%20after%20permission%20from%20authority%20concerned.%20But%20the%20use%20of%20any%20amplifier%20or%20loudspeaker%20on%20any%20private%20vehicle%20or%20building%20or%20a%20public%20area%20is%20prohibited%20unless%20specifically%20allowed.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20order%20adds%20that%20vehicles%20moving%20between%20Haryana%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Delhi%20will%20be%20thoroughly%20inspected%20at%20checkpoints.%20It%20also%20says%20the%20dissemination%20of%20any%20provocative%20slogan%20or%20message%20through%20verbal%2C%20written%20or%20electronic%20means%20will%20be%20considered%20unlawful.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20Police%20has%20said%20non-compliance%20of%20the%20order%20will%20attract%20criminal%20prosecution%20under%20Section%20188%2C%20relating%20to%20disobedience%20of%20an%20order%20issued%20by%20a%20public%20servant.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707726060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fhblfsfio_delhi-border_625x300_12_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Ffarmers-protest-delhi-police-section-144-weddings-to-loudspeakers-whats-allowed-in-delhi-ahead-of-farmers-march-5041980%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Determined%20to%20prevent%20any%20law%20and%20order%20situation%20due%20to%20the%20mega%20farmers'%20march%20tomorrow%2C%20Delhi%20Police%20today%20clamped%20prohibitory%20orders%20for%20a%20month%2C%20banning%20public%20processions%20and%20bringing%20several%20other%20restrictions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Ffarmers-protest-delhi-police-section-144-weddings-to-loudspeakers-whats-allowed-in-delhi-ahead-of-farmers-march-5041980%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Ffarmers-protest-delhi-police-section-144-weddings-to-loudspeakers-whats-allowed-in-delhi-ahead-of-farmers-march-5041980%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Ffarmers-protest-delhi-police-section-144-weddings-to-loudspeakers-whats-allowed-in-delhi-ahead-of-farmers-march-5041980%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20Atheist%E2%80%99%20Who%20Cracked%20the%20Glass%20Ceiling%20in%20UK%20Politics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F12131838%2F1200px-Official_portrait_of_Baroness_Flather_crop_2_2019.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20prime%20ministers%20of%20Britain%20and%20of%20Ireland%20both%20visited%20Belfast%20in%20British-ruled%20Northern%20Ireland%20the%20other%20day.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%2C%20is%20of%20Punjabi%20descent%3B%20the%20other%2C%20Leo%20Varadkar%2C%20has%20family%20roots%20in%20Mumbai%20where%20he%20spent%20part%20of%20his%20childhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20occasion%20was%20the%20restoration%20of%20devolved%20government%20in%20Northern%20Ireland%20after%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20of%20political%20stalemate.%20A%20big%20event%20%E2%80%93%20but%20I%20want%20to%20dwell%20on%20the%20subject%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20touched%20on%20in%20the%20news%20coverage.%20No%20one%20commented%20on%20these%20two%20prime%20ministers%20both%20being%20of%20Indian%20heritage.%20It%20is%2C%20quite%20literally%2C%20unremarkable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20of%20immigrants%20are%20now%20so%20prominent%20in%20British%20(and%20Irish)%20public%20life%2C%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20forget%20just%20how%20unrelentingly%20white%20the%20political%20landscape%20was%20just%20a%20generation%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20I%20landed%20what%20I%20regarded%20then%20as%20my%20dream%20job.%20I%20became%20a%20BBC%20political%20correspondent.%20In%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%2C%20there%20were%20just%20four%20Black%20and%20Asian%20Members%20of%20Parliament.%20And%20all%20four%20were%20still%20then%20newcomers%20to%20Westminster.%20There%20had%20been%20Indian%20MPs%20in%20earlier%20years%20%E2%80%93%20men%20such%20as%20Dadabhai%20Naoroji%20and%20Shapurji%20Saklatvala%20%E2%80%93%20but%20for%20decades%20until%20the%201987%20election%2C%20the%20Commons%20had%20been%20entirely%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20was%20still%20reporting%20on%20Westminster%20when%20Shreela%20Flather%20%E2%80%93%20who%20died%20last%20week%20just%20short%20of%20her%2090th%20birthday%20%E2%80%93%20was%20nominated%20to%20the%20unelected%20upper%20chamber%20of%20Parliament%2C%20the%20House%20of%20Lords.%20That%20was%20in%201990.%20She%20was%20the%20first%20Asian%20woman%20to%20take%20a%20seat%20in%20the%20Lords.%20She%20had%20earlier%20been%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20first%20Asian%20woman%20magistrate%20and%20the%20first%20Asian%20woman%20to%20be%20a%20local%20mayor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20her%20elevation%20to%20the%20Lords%2C%20the%20number%20of%20ethnic%20minority%20peers%20doubled.%20The%20other%20minority%20peer%20back%20then%20was%20Lord%20Pitt%2C%20a%20doctor%20and%20Labour%20politician%20who%20was%20born%20in%20Grenada%20in%20the%20Caribbean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaroness%20Flather%2C%20a%20Conservative%2C%20was%20at%20that%20time%20her%20party%E2%80%99s%20only%20non-white%20parliamentarian%20in%20either%20the%20Commons%20or%20the%20Lords.%20She%20made%20herself%20noticed%2C%20not%20least%20by%20wearing%20a%20sari%20in%20the%20ever-so-formal%20setting%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20chamber.%20She%20was%20not%20a%20political%20heavyweight%3B%20she%20was%20never%20a%20government%20minister.%20But%20she%20was%20friendly%2C%20accessible%20%E2%80%93%20and%20determined%20to%20make%20her%20mark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20she%20succeeded.%20Not%20many%20parliamentarians%20can%20point%20to%20something%20that%20is%20their%20particular%20achievement.%20But%20her%20energetic%20advocacy%20of%20and%20fund-raising%20for%20a%20memorial%20to%20the%20five-million%20soldiers%2C%20sailors%20and%20airmen%20from%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%2C%20Africa%20and%20the%20Caribbean%20who%20served%20in%20two%20world%20wars%20was%20crowned%20with%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Memorial%20Gates%20close%20to%20Buckingham%20Palace%20were%20inaugurated%20by%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20in%202002.%20A%20commemorative%20event%20is%20held%20there%20every%20March%20on%20Commonwealth%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20brought%20up%20a%20Hindu%2C%20Shreela%20Flather%20regarded%20herself%20as%20an%20atheist%20(or%20sometimes%20as%20a%20Hindu%20atheist%2C%20which%20of%20course%20is%20not%20quite%20such%20a%20contradiction%20as%20it%20would%20be%20for%20other%20global%20religions).%20She%20supported%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20National%20Secular%20Society%20and%20Humanists%20UK%20which%20campaign%20against%20the%20influence%20of%20organised%20religion%20in%20public%20life.%20She%20also%20was%20for%20many%20years%20the%20chair%20of%20Marie%20Stopes%20International%2C%20which%20provides%20sexual%20and%20reproductive%20health%20information.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20normal%20range%20of%20causes%20for%20a%20Conservative%20peer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20had%20a%20compelling%20back%20story.%20Baroness%20Flather%20was%20born%20Shreela%20Rai%20into%20a%20prosperous%20Hindu%20family%20in%20Lahore.%20Sir%20Ganga%20Ram%2C%20the%20celebrated%20Punjabi%20civil%20engineer%20and%20philanthropist%2C%20was%20her%20great-grandfather.%20At%20Partition%2C%20the%20family%20fled%20to%20Delhi.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20Shreela%E2%80%99s%20father%20was%20appointed%20India%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20Brazil.%20She%20came%20to%20London%20to%20study%20law%20in%201952.%20Her%20first%20husband%20had%20been%20a%20captain%20in%20the%20British%20army.%20That%20marriage%20ended%20in%20divorce.%20Her%20second%20husband%2C%20a%20British%20barrister%2C%20died%20seven%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShreela%20Flather%20took%20up%20issues%20of%20importance%20to%20British%20Asians%20%E2%80%93%20for%20example%2C%20seeking%20to%20change%20rules%20on%20school%20uniform%20which%20discriminated%20against%20Asian%20pupils.%20She%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Race%20Relations%20Board%20and%20later%20the%20Commission%20for%20Racial%20Equality.%20She%20described%20the%20police%20as%20%E2%80%98institutionally%20racist%E2%80%99%20before%20the%20full%20weight%20of%20police%20prejudice%20against%20people%20of%20colour%20was%20widely%20understood.%20And%20she%20had%20to%20face%20racism%20within%20her%20own%20party.%20It%E2%80%99s%20said%20that%20when%20she%20first%20spoke%20at%20a%20Conservative%20Party%20conference%2C%20she%20was%20spat%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Flather%E2%80%99s%20views%2C%20however%2C%20were%20themselves%20denounced%20as%20racist.%20She%20called%20for%20DNA%20tests%20to%20combat%20the%20practice%20among%20some%20Muslim%20communities%20of%20first%20cousins%20marrying.%20She%20proposed%20a%20ban%20on%20halal%20meat.%20And%20she%20commented%20that%20some%20immigrant%20groups%2C%20particularly%20those%20from%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh%2C%20deliberately%20had%20lots%20of%20children%20so%20they%20could%20claim%20more%20in%20welfare%20benefits.%20Indian%20families%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20%E2%80%93%20she%20said%20%E2%80%93%20%C2%A0%E2%80%98are%20like%20the%20Jews%20of%20old.%20They%20want%20their%20children%20to%20be%20educated.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20had%20a%20reputation%20for%20%E2%80%98saying%20the%20unsayable%E2%80%99%2C%20she%20conceded%20that%20she%20had%20on%20occasions%20%E2%80%98gone%20too%20far%E2%80%99.%20And%20she%20certainly%20caused%20offence%20to%20British%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaroness%20Flather%20left%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20in%202008%2C%20continuing%20to%20sit%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20without%20a%20party%20affiliation.%20She%20was%20unquestionably%20a%20pioneer%2C%20with%20the%20strength%20of%20character%20to%20succeed%20in%20areas%20which%20were%20not%20then%20welcoming%20to%20Asians%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20to%20Asian%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20managed%20to%20crack%20the%20glass%20ceiling%20that%20hitherto%20had%20constrained%20the%20rise%20in%20politics%20of%20British%20Asians%2C%20however%20talented.%20There%20are%20now%2066%20MPs%20and%2055%20members%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20who%20are%20from%20an%20ethnic%20minority.%20Rishi%20Sunak%20and%20others%20have%20smashed%20that%20glass%20ceiling%20into%20tiny%20pieces.%20But%20in%20doing%20so%20they%20were%20standing%20on%20the%20shoulders%2C%20metaphorically%20at%20least%2C%20of%20the%20diminutive%20Shreela%20Flather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Ffrino%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Whitehead%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20honorary%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nottingham%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20a%20former%20BBC%20India%20correspondent.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%20Calling%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0How%20does%20India%20look%20from%20afar%3F%20Looming%20world%20power%20or%20dysfunctional%20democracy%3F%20And%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20Britain%2C%20and%20the%20West%2C%20that%20India%20needs%20to%20know%20about%20and%20perhaps%20learn%20from%3F%20This%20fortnightly%20column%20helps%20forge%20the%20connections%20so%20essential%20in%20our%20globalising%20world.%