ry%20has%20been%20actively%20trying%20to%20bolster%20its%20declining%20birth%20rates.%20China%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fthe-end-of-chinas-one-child-policy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edropped%20its%20controversial%20one-child%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016%2C%20allowing%20couples%20to%20have%20two%20kids.%20The%20government%20changed%20the%20rules%20again%20in%202021.%20Now%2C%20couples%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F05%2F31%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Fchina-three-child-policy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20up%20to%20three%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20measures%2C%20however%2C%20haven't%20achieved%20the%20desired%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20because%20most%20of%20China's%20fertility%20reduction%2C%20especially%20since%20the%201990s%2C%20has%20been%20voluntary%20and%20more%20of%20a%20result%20of%20modernization%20than%20fertility%20control%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fliberalarts.tamu.edu%2Fsociology%2Fprofile%2Fdudley-poston%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDudley%20L.%20Poston%20Jr.%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20sociology%20professor%20at%20Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20University%2C%20said%20in%20a%20commentary%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fchina-needs-immigrants-208911%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChinese%20couples%20are%20having%20fewer%20children%20due%20to%20the%20higher%20living%20costs%20and%20educational%20expenses%20involved%20in%20having%20more%20than%20one%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPain%20and%20gain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20all%20about%20money.%20Having%20children%20remains%20a%20deeply%20personal%20decision%20that%20can't%20be%20evaluated%20by%20finances%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%2C%20the%20venture%20capital%20analyst%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20didn't%20want%20to%20experience%20the%20pain%20of%20childbirth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20now%20know%2C%20via%20social%20media%20and%20online%20forums%2C%20about%20how%20painful%20it%20is%20to%20give%20birth%20to%20a%20child.%20This%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20information%20that%20is%20absent%20when%20a%20girl%20is%20growing%20up%20because%20mothers%20probably%20don't%20talk%20about%20the%20pain%20of%20giving%20birth%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20mum%20didn't%20say%20that%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I'm%20pretty%20sure%20my%20grandmother%20didn't%20tell%20her%20either%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20not%20everyone%20is%20opposed%20to%20having%20children.%20Some%20talked%20about%20the%20joy%20that%20comes%20with%20watching%20their%20kid%20grow%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20a%20child%20is%20a%20blessing%20that%20brings%20joy%2C%20although%20it%20can%20be%20a%20hassle%20at%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20person%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweibo.com%2F6633074403%2FNuGdqB734%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWeibo%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BRich%20or%20poor%2C%20we've%20just%20got%20to%20take%20it%20one%20step%20at%20a%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELanjie%20Wang%2C%2025%2C%20an%20economics%20graduate%20student%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20would%20like%20to%20have%20children%20someday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20have%20children%20because%20I%20think%20I%20have%20brought%20happiness%20to%20my%20parents.%20I%20believe%20that%20my%20children%20will%20bring%20my%20family%20happiness%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Wang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBaby%20booms%20won't%20offer%20a%20quick%20fix%20to%20China's%20problems%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20China%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20facing%20a%20demographic%20ticking%20time%20bomb.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-birthrate-reaches-record-low-billions-spent-2023-6%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOnly%2520770%252C747%2520b